1
00:00:04,306 --> 00:00:08,746
[♪]

2
00:01:06,430 --> 00:01:08,165
[HORSE NEIGHING]

3
00:01:08,199 --> 00:01:10,368
ASTRO:
So.

4
00:01:10,402 --> 00:01:11,737
Who's
this Blue Knight guy?

5
00:01:11,770 --> 00:01:12,906
DELIVERY ROBOT:
He's a robot.

6
00:01:12,939 --> 00:01:13,941
But that's all
anyone knows.

7
00:01:13,974 --> 00:01:16,677
There have been some rumors
going around, though.

8
00:01:16,712 --> 00:01:19,348
W-what rumors?

9
00:01:19,381 --> 00:01:20,617
Well, you didn't hear it
from me,

10
00:01:20,650 --> 00:01:21,752
but I heard

11
00:01:21,785 --> 00:01:23,822
the Blue Knight secretly
attacked a robot transport boat

12
00:01:23,855 --> 00:01:25,357
in the middle of the night

13
00:01:25,390 --> 00:01:27,894
and then took out an entire
shipping warehouse.

14
00:01:29,530 --> 00:01:32,300
WOMAN:
Still behind me, huh?

15
00:01:32,334 --> 00:01:33,336
DELIVERY ROBOT:
You don't want

16
00:01:33,369 --> 00:01:34,904
to be on his bad side,

17
00:01:34,938 --> 00:01:39,411
because the Blue Knight
will take on anyone, anywhere.

18
00:01:39,445 --> 00:01:41,347
Sounds like this guy
is a big bully.

19
00:01:41,380 --> 00:01:42,449
No.

20
00:01:42,482 --> 00:01:43,817
He's fighting to save robots

21
00:01:43,851 --> 00:01:45,854
that are being mistreated
by their masters.

22
00:01:45,887 --> 00:01:48,290
He doesn't care what laws
he has to break either.

23
00:01:48,323 --> 00:01:53,331
Whatever you do,
don't try to stop him.

24
00:02:01,577 --> 00:02:03,279
WOMAN:
Target sighted.

25
00:02:03,312 --> 00:02:05,616
Astro!

26
00:02:05,649 --> 00:02:08,287
MAN [OVER RADIO]:
<i>Initiate transformation.</i>

27
00:02:12,325 --> 00:02:13,394
[GIRLISHLY]
Help me!

28
00:02:13,427 --> 00:02:14,428
[GASPING FEARFULLY]

29
00:02:14,462 --> 00:02:16,464
Help me! Help me!

30
00:02:16,498 --> 00:02:18,534
[GRUNTS]

31
00:02:18,567 --> 00:02:19,970
Oh?

32
00:02:20,004 --> 00:02:21,872
Help me!

33
00:02:21,906 --> 00:02:24,510
Help me!

34
00:02:24,543 --> 00:02:25,845
What's the matter?

35
00:02:25,878 --> 00:02:27,981
The Blue Knight!
He's chasing me.

36
00:02:28,015 --> 00:02:29,250
The Blue Knight?
Where?

37
00:02:29,283 --> 00:02:31,320
Up there. There!

38
00:02:41,067 --> 00:02:43,270
Wow! That must be him.

39
00:02:43,303 --> 00:02:46,575
[SIREN WAILING]

40
00:02:46,608 --> 00:02:48,478
[HORSE NEIGHING]

41
00:02:49,580 --> 00:02:51,750
Oh!

42
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:55,822
I'll go up there and--

43
00:02:55,856 --> 00:02:57,291
No, don't.

44
00:02:57,324 --> 00:02:59,060
It's all right now.
You've saved me.

45
00:02:59,093 --> 00:03:00,996
I've been reading
all about you in the papers.

46
00:03:01,029 --> 00:03:02,331
You're a real hero.

47
00:03:02,365 --> 00:03:03,567
I'm grateful to you.

48
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:05,870
Oh, I didn't do anything.

49
00:03:05,903 --> 00:03:07,639
Well, you're a hero to me.

50
00:03:07,673 --> 00:03:10,577
Please, let me
shake your hand.

51
00:03:10,610 --> 00:03:13,347
I'll never forget this, Astro.
You're incredible.

52
00:03:19,356 --> 00:03:20,825
Astro, you fool.

53
00:03:20,858 --> 00:03:24,430
If only everything
was this easy.

54
00:03:24,463 --> 00:03:26,333
MAN: You sound
a little worried.

55
00:03:26,366 --> 00:03:27,435
Worried?

56
00:03:27,468 --> 00:03:29,004
Yeah.

57
00:03:29,037 --> 00:03:31,541
Not afraid of that big blue guy
on the horse, are you?

58
00:03:31,574 --> 00:03:34,011
Quiet! The Blue Knight
doesn't scare me.

59
00:03:34,044 --> 00:03:37,116
I've handled robots
that were worse than him.

60
00:03:37,149 --> 00:03:38,751
MAN:
Katari!

61
00:03:38,784 --> 00:03:40,386
It is extremely important to me

62
00:03:40,420 --> 00:03:43,625
that the Blue Knight doesn't
find out about our plan.

63
00:03:43,658 --> 00:03:47,364
He could ruin everything.
Do you understand that?

64
00:03:47,397 --> 00:03:49,700
Yes.
Completely.

65
00:03:49,734 --> 00:03:51,603
Very good.

66
00:03:51,637 --> 00:03:56,577
Now I'm almost ready to put
Project <i>Mach Fifteen</i> in motion.

67
00:03:56,610 --> 00:03:59,681
And once I do, there won't be
time for these petty arguments.

68
00:03:59,715 --> 00:04:01,451
If this project's a success,

69
00:04:01,484 --> 00:04:03,119
the world will be
a much different place.

70
00:04:03,154 --> 00:04:04,822
Because there won't be

71
00:04:04,856 --> 00:04:06,892
any more of those obnoxious
robots around to question us!

72
00:04:12,133 --> 00:04:14,403
CAPTAIN [OVER SPEAKER]:
<i>I want to thank you all</i>

73
00:04:14,436 --> 00:04:16,974
<i>for flying</i>
<i>on the</i> Mach Fifteen <i>today.</i>

74
00:04:17,007 --> 00:04:18,809
Right now,
we're passing over

75
00:04:18,842 --> 00:04:20,912
the brand-new
Sonic Shuttles Launch Center.

76
00:04:20,945 --> 00:04:23,516
And if you look to the left,

77
00:04:23,549 --> 00:04:26,153
<i>you'll see the Green Glade</i>
<i>housing development,</i>

78
00:04:26,187 --> 00:04:30,526
<i>where new homes</i>
<i>are priced very reasonably.</i>

79
00:04:30,559 --> 00:04:33,431
Ah! Oh!

80
00:04:33,464 --> 00:04:34,465
Cocoa, sir?
Sure.

81
00:04:34,499 --> 00:04:36,034
When do we arrive?

82
00:04:36,067 --> 00:04:39,106
Our estimated time of arrival
is half an hour.

83
00:04:39,139 --> 00:04:40,641
Perfect.

84
00:04:40,674 --> 00:04:41,743
I'll make the conference

85
00:04:41,776 --> 00:04:42,977
with plenty of time
to spare, hmm?

86
00:04:44,880 --> 00:04:45,782
MAN [OVER RADIO]:
<i>Hello!</i>

87
00:04:45,816 --> 00:04:47,551
<i>August City</i>
<i>Airport Control.</i>

88
00:04:47,584 --> 00:04:48,786
WOMAN [OVER RADIO]:
<i>I advise you</i>

89
00:04:48,820 --> 00:04:49,721
<i>to listen very carefully.</i>

90
00:04:49,754 --> 00:04:50,823
MAN:
Who is this?

91
00:04:50,856 --> 00:04:52,491
Please identify yourself.

92
00:04:52,525 --> 00:04:54,194
Ma'am, I repeat, who are you?

93
00:04:54,228 --> 00:04:56,464
WOMAN:
<i>Enough. Pay close attention.</i>

94
00:04:56,497 --> 00:04:58,200
<i>There's a wormhole projector</i>
<i>on the</i> Mach Fifteen--

95
00:04:58,234 --> 00:05:01,238
What? A wormhole projector?

96
00:05:01,271 --> 00:05:02,239
Oh, no.

97
00:05:02,272 --> 00:05:03,908
A thing like that
could send

98
00:05:03,942 --> 00:05:05,177
the <i>Mach Fifteen</i>
into another dimension.

99
00:05:05,210 --> 00:05:06,746
It could.

100
00:05:06,779 --> 00:05:09,082
But how do we know this nutcase
is telling the truth?

101
00:05:09,115 --> 00:05:10,952
Hey, give us some proof here.

102
00:05:10,985 --> 00:05:13,722
<i>You want proof?</i>
<i>Just look out your window.</i>

103
00:05:13,756 --> 00:05:14,991
[GULPS]

104
00:05:22,068 --> 00:05:24,037
MAN:
Wow! What's that up there?

105
00:05:24,071 --> 00:05:26,875
[HIGH-PITCHED WHIRRING]

106
00:05:52,245 --> 00:05:54,215
Mach Ten! Mach Ten!
Come in! Come in!

107
00:05:54,248 --> 00:05:55,817
Al,
it's all right.

108
00:05:55,850 --> 00:05:58,221
It's being repaired.
There was nobody onboard.

109
00:05:58,254 --> 00:06:00,690
WOMAN [OVER RADIO]:
That was just a demonstration.

110
00:06:00,724 --> 00:06:03,028
<i>But we'll do the same thing</i>
<i>to the</i> Mach Fifteen

111
00:06:03,061 --> 00:06:04,864
<i>and all its passengers</i>

112
00:06:04,897 --> 00:06:06,899
<i>unless you give us</i>
<i>everything we ask for.</i>

113
00:06:06,934 --> 00:06:10,605
<i>We'll contact you again soon</i>
<i>with our demands.</i>

114
00:06:10,639 --> 00:06:11,841
Listen, lady.

115
00:06:11,874 --> 00:06:13,309
When the police find out
who you are,

116
00:06:13,343 --> 00:06:15,145
you're going to be
in big trouble.

117
00:06:15,178 --> 00:06:18,050
<i>The police can't do</i>
<i>anything to me.</i>

118
00:06:21,721 --> 00:06:22,857
DETECTIVE TAWASHI:
Two wormhole projectors

119
00:06:22,890 --> 00:06:26,161
were stolen from
the university last week,

120
00:06:26,195 --> 00:06:28,598
so she means business.

121
00:06:28,631 --> 00:06:30,734
If the <i>Mach Fifteen</i>
changes course or altitude,

122
00:06:30,768 --> 00:06:32,203
she says the projector
will activate.

123
00:06:32,236 --> 00:06:34,607
And another thing.

124
00:06:34,640 --> 00:06:37,844
There's a huge storm brewing
right in <i>Mach Fifteen's</i> path.

125
00:06:37,879 --> 00:06:39,681
You all have to
get to the <i>Mach Fifteen</i>

126
00:06:39,714 --> 00:06:40,816
before it hits that storm.

127
00:06:40,849 --> 00:06:42,151
Find a way in

128
00:06:42,185 --> 00:06:43,887
and then dismantle
that wormhole projector.

129
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:44,922
POLICEMAN:
Inspector! Look at the monitor.

130
00:06:44,955 --> 00:06:45,923
We're being signal-jacked.

131
00:06:45,956 --> 00:06:47,158
Huh?

132
00:06:47,192 --> 00:06:49,996
[STATIC CRACKLING]

133
00:06:51,398 --> 00:06:53,968
<i>We are</i>
<i>the Robot Liberation Army.</i>

134
00:06:54,002 --> 00:06:55,670
Huh?

135
00:06:55,704 --> 00:06:57,874
<i>We put the wormhole projector</i>

136
00:06:57,908 --> 00:06:59,676
<i>on the</i> Mach Fifteen.

137
00:06:59,710 --> 00:07:02,414
[ALL GASPING]

138
00:07:02,447 --> 00:07:05,184
I have a horrible feeling
about this.

139
00:07:05,218 --> 00:07:06,787
<i>Our demands are simple.</i>

140
00:07:06,821 --> 00:07:08,689
<i>Every robot is to be set free</i>
<i>from its owner</i>

141
00:07:08,723 --> 00:07:10,960
<i>immediately.</i>

142
00:07:10,993 --> 00:07:13,897
Or we'll activate
<i>the wormhole projector</i>

143
00:07:13,931 --> 00:07:16,300
<i>and that will be the end</i>
<i>of the</i> Mach Fifteen.

144
00:07:16,334 --> 00:07:17,369
[GASPS]

145
00:07:17,402 --> 00:07:18,704
She'll pay for this!

146
00:07:18,738 --> 00:07:21,375
[ALL MUTTERING]

147
00:07:21,408 --> 00:07:23,345
<i>The Robot Liberation Army</i>

148
00:07:23,378 --> 00:07:27,016
has the support of the world's
<i>most powerful robots,</i>

149
00:07:27,050 --> 00:07:28,318
<i>including the greatest</i>
<i>of them all,</i>

150
00:07:28,352 --> 00:07:30,188
<i>Astro.</i>

151
00:07:30,221 --> 00:07:31,422
[GASPS]

152
00:07:31,456 --> 00:07:33,392
That's a lie!

153
00:07:33,425 --> 00:07:34,694
I've only met her once.

154
00:07:34,727 --> 00:07:35,929
ASTRO:
She asked me for help!

155
00:07:35,963 --> 00:07:37,098
WOMAN:
<i>Astro has assured us</i>

156
00:07:37,131 --> 00:07:38,700
<i>we will succeed.</i>

157
00:07:38,733 --> 00:07:41,404
Astro?

158
00:07:44,208 --> 00:07:46,044
MAN 1:
I was afraid this would happen.

159
00:07:46,078 --> 00:07:48,882
MAN 2: See what happens
when you give them <i>kokoru?</i>

160
00:07:48,915 --> 00:07:51,952
Well, for sure,
you can't trust a robot.

161
00:07:51,986 --> 00:07:55,224
Astro's betrayed
everyone who's ever helped him.

162
00:07:55,257 --> 00:07:58,228
He's living proof
that robots can't be trusted.

163
00:07:58,261 --> 00:08:00,164
DRAKE [OVER TV]:
<i>We humans need to mobilize</i>

164
00:08:00,198 --> 00:08:01,934
<i>before it's too late.</i>

165
00:08:01,967 --> 00:08:05,940
<i>Stand up! Fight the robots!</i>
<i>Eliminate all of them.</i>

166
00:08:05,973 --> 00:08:09,945
<i>Otherwise they'll take over,</i>
<i>and we'll be serving them!</i>

167
00:08:09,978 --> 00:08:11,080
MAN [OVER AIRSHIP INTERCOM]:
<i>Detective Tawashi!</i>

168
00:08:11,114 --> 00:08:13,884
<i>We've located Astro</i>
<i>and are in pursuit.</i>

169
00:08:17,523 --> 00:08:19,326
I'm sorry
about this, Astro.

170
00:08:19,359 --> 00:08:21,495
But I've been ordered
to drain your energy.

171
00:08:21,529 --> 00:08:23,165
This is all a mistake.

172
00:08:23,198 --> 00:08:25,768
I should be helping those people
on the <i>Mach Fifteen.</i>

173
00:08:25,801 --> 00:08:28,239
Don't you worry
about the <i>Mach Fifteen.</i>

174
00:08:28,272 --> 00:08:30,976
We're sending a rescue team
up there to help them right now.

175
00:08:31,009 --> 00:08:33,412
And it's going to be
a human rescue team.

176
00:08:33,447 --> 00:08:35,783
No robots allowed.

177
00:08:35,816 --> 00:08:38,787
You just rest
right here, Astro.

178
00:08:40,222 --> 00:08:42,159
But wait!
Detective, wait!

179
00:08:42,192 --> 00:08:43,026
[GROANING]

180
00:08:46,198 --> 00:08:48,468
Huh...

181
00:08:48,501 --> 00:08:49,836
[GROANING]

182
00:08:59,150 --> 00:09:00,286
NEWSCASTER:
<i>There have been</i>

183
00:09:00,319 --> 00:09:02,188
<i>dozens of anti-robot</i>
<i>demonstrations already.</i>

184
00:09:02,221 --> 00:09:05,193
<i>And more</i>
<i>are reportedly planned.</i>

185
00:09:05,226 --> 00:09:06,360
That's perfect!

186
00:09:06,394 --> 00:09:08,197
Guys, let's go.

187
00:09:08,230 --> 00:09:10,366
Get rid of that overgrown
marionette for me.

188
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:12,536
MAN:
Yes, sir!

189
00:09:22,384 --> 00:09:23,352
It's all your fault

190
00:09:23,385 --> 00:09:25,588
for making those robots
in the first place.

191
00:09:25,622 --> 00:09:27,458
Now they're trying
to take over the world

192
00:09:27,491 --> 00:09:29,528
and your little Astro
is right in the lead.

193
00:09:29,561 --> 00:09:31,497
Oh! Calm down, sir!
Huh?

194
00:09:31,531 --> 00:09:32,565
MAN:
Back off, robot!

195
00:09:32,599 --> 00:09:34,568
Are you all right?

196
00:09:34,601 --> 00:09:36,939
You should be
ashamed of yourself.

197
00:09:36,972 --> 00:09:38,574
She didn't do
anything to you.

198
00:09:38,607 --> 00:09:41,178
And Astro hasn't done
anything to you either.

199
00:09:41,211 --> 00:09:44,115
You're right. He hasn't
done anything to me.

200
00:09:44,149 --> 00:09:47,921
And I'll make sure
he never gets the chance.

201
00:09:47,955 --> 00:09:49,090
[ASTRO GROANING]

202
00:09:53,162 --> 00:09:56,433
If-- If I had more energy,
I could help all those people.

203
00:09:56,467 --> 00:09:58,603
[ALARM WAILING]

204
00:09:58,636 --> 00:10:00,106
Huh?

205
00:10:08,651 --> 00:10:10,320
ASTRO:
Blue Knight!

206
00:10:10,353 --> 00:10:13,458
I am not your enemy, Astro.
I came here to help you.

207
00:10:13,492 --> 00:10:14,527
[GRUNTS]

208
00:10:20,602 --> 00:10:23,707
All the energy you need
is in there.

209
00:10:23,740 --> 00:10:27,112
The choice is yours.

210
00:10:30,583 --> 00:10:33,020
[ALL GRUNTING]

211
00:10:35,089 --> 00:10:38,028
That--
That was the Blue Knight!

212
00:10:43,101 --> 00:10:44,237
COMMANDER [OVER RADIO]:
<i>Airship</i> Mach Fifteen!

213
00:10:44,270 --> 00:10:47,007
<i>This is the air police.</i>

214
00:10:52,181 --> 00:10:55,386
This is airship <i>Mach Fifteen.</i>

215
00:10:55,419 --> 00:10:59,325
Hurry! Please! We're headed
right for the storm.

216
00:10:59,359 --> 00:11:01,227
COMMANDER [OVER RADIO]:
<i>Unit Two. Status report.</i>

217
00:11:01,261 --> 00:11:02,697
PILOT [OVER RADIO]:
<i>This wind's</i>

218
00:11:02,730 --> 00:11:05,167
<i>going to make it hard to</i>
<i>transfer to the</i> Mach Fifteen.

219
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:08,172
So, what are we going to do?

220
00:11:08,205 --> 00:11:09,740
PILOT: <i>Commander,</i>
<i>somebody's closing on us fast.</i>

221
00:11:09,774 --> 00:11:11,109
COMMANDER:
Who?

222
00:11:11,142 --> 00:11:12,243
PILOT:
<i>It's--</i>

223
00:11:12,277 --> 00:11:15,182
<i>It looks like Astro</i>
<i>and the Blue Knight.</i>

224
00:11:15,215 --> 00:11:17,718
CAPTAIN [OVER RADIO]:
<i>Now we're in real trouble.</i>

225
00:11:19,087 --> 00:11:20,255
Look out.
Huh?

226
00:11:24,328 --> 00:11:26,598
Blue Knight! On your left!
Be careful!

227
00:11:26,631 --> 00:11:29,636
[SHOTS FIRING]

228
00:11:32,307 --> 00:11:34,109
PILOT [OVER RADIO]:
<i>Astro and the Blue Knight</i>

229
00:11:34,142 --> 00:11:35,011
<i>are headed towards</i>
<i>the</i> Mach Fifteen.

230
00:11:35,044 --> 00:11:36,278
MAN [OVER RADIO]:
<i>Not for long.</i>

231
00:11:39,650 --> 00:11:41,220
<i>Locked on target.</i>

232
00:11:41,253 --> 00:11:42,221
COMMANDER [OVER RADIO]:
<i>Careful now!</i>

233
00:11:42,254 --> 00:11:44,057
[MAN YELLING]

234
00:11:44,090 --> 00:11:45,359
No! Whoa!

235
00:11:48,296 --> 00:11:51,467
[YELLS]

236
00:11:51,501 --> 00:11:54,238
We're losing power in our
portside antigravity engine.

237
00:11:54,272 --> 00:11:57,276
Activate auxiliary engines!
Maintain altitude!

238
00:11:57,309 --> 00:11:59,412
Somebody tell me
what's going on up there.

239
00:11:59,446 --> 00:12:00,781
PILOT [OVER RADIO]:
<i>Commander!</i>

240
00:12:00,814 --> 00:12:03,151
<i>Look up ahead.</i>
<i>The storm clouds.</i>

241
00:12:05,220 --> 00:12:07,290
COMMANDER:
<i>I have never seen</i>
<i>so much lightning.</i>

242
00:12:07,324 --> 00:12:10,162
CAPTAIN:
No way to avoid it now.

243
00:12:11,530 --> 00:12:14,234
COMMANDER [OVER RADIO]:
<i>Rescue team, pull back!</i>

244
00:12:16,304 --> 00:12:17,706
What's happening?

245
00:12:17,739 --> 00:12:19,241
We're going
right into the storm.

246
00:12:20,443 --> 00:12:22,279
Astro!

247
00:12:22,312 --> 00:12:24,215
I can't believe
you're here.

248
00:12:24,248 --> 00:12:26,118
[ALL MURMURING]

249
00:12:26,151 --> 00:12:27,587
Everybody, listen!

250
00:12:27,620 --> 00:12:30,324
The Robot Liberation Army
doesn't exist.

251
00:12:30,357 --> 00:12:33,128
It's just a trick by some people
who hate robots.

252
00:12:33,161 --> 00:12:34,763
Now it's all starting
to make sense.

253
00:12:34,797 --> 00:12:37,635
We have to find that wormhole
projector right away.

254
00:12:37,668 --> 00:12:38,903
Why should I believe
any of this?

255
00:12:38,936 --> 00:12:40,238
You're just
a stinking--

256
00:12:40,271 --> 00:12:41,507
[YELLS]

257
00:12:41,540 --> 00:12:42,675
Oh!

258
00:12:42,709 --> 00:12:44,177
[ALL SCREAMING]

259
00:12:44,211 --> 00:12:44,945
WOMAN:
What's happening? Oh, no!

260
00:12:48,317 --> 00:12:49,885
WOMAN: Everyone,
please calm down.

261
00:12:49,919 --> 00:12:51,321
There's no reason
to panic.

262
00:12:51,355 --> 00:12:53,290
Go back and fasten
your seat belts.

263
00:12:56,395 --> 00:12:57,564
FEMALE FIRST OFFICER:
Temperature rising

264
00:12:57,597 --> 00:12:59,333
in starboard engine.

265
00:12:59,366 --> 00:13:01,569
Do what you can
to keep it running.

266
00:13:01,602 --> 00:13:02,871
Captain!

267
00:13:02,904 --> 00:13:05,242
Is there any sign
of the wormhole projector?

268
00:13:05,275 --> 00:13:06,877
No. We couldn't find
a trace of it.

269
00:13:06,910 --> 00:13:08,279
Doctor?

270
00:13:08,312 --> 00:13:10,249
Maybe it's on
the outside of the ship.

271
00:13:10,282 --> 00:13:12,218
Hmm.

272
00:13:12,252 --> 00:13:16,224
O'SHAY [OVER RADIO]:
<i>Astro, can you hear me?</i>

273
00:13:16,258 --> 00:13:21,198
<i>Use your spectra-graphic</i>
<i>vision, but be very careful.</i>

274
00:13:21,231 --> 00:13:24,603
<i>If that projector</i>
<i>is activated--</i>

275
00:13:24,636 --> 00:13:25,772
ASTRO:
There!

276
00:13:31,646 --> 00:13:33,248
Huh?

277
00:13:33,282 --> 00:13:35,786
I've found the projector,
doctor.

278
00:13:35,819 --> 00:13:37,188
O'SHAY:
<i>Good work, Astro.</i>

279
00:13:43,497 --> 00:13:46,735
DRAKE: So, Astro.
You've found the device.

280
00:13:46,768 --> 00:13:50,240
I have a feeling
you're going to wish you hadn't.

281
00:13:50,273 --> 00:13:51,709
[GROANING]

282
00:13:51,742 --> 00:13:52,644
[ELECTRONIC RINGING]

283
00:13:52,677 --> 00:13:54,446
Huh?

284
00:13:54,479 --> 00:13:58,219
Oh, no! It's set to activate
if it's removed!

285
00:14:02,358 --> 00:14:04,428
Great job, Astro.
Now throw it!

286
00:14:04,461 --> 00:14:05,730
[GRUNTS]

287
00:14:05,763 --> 00:14:08,834
[GRUNTING]

288
00:14:13,073 --> 00:14:14,576
[GRUNTS]

289
00:14:21,418 --> 00:14:23,321
Oh, no! It's the wormhole!

290
00:14:35,506 --> 00:14:37,709
We're being pulled
into the wormhole!

291
00:14:37,742 --> 00:14:38,778
[GROANING]

292
00:14:38,811 --> 00:14:41,715
[ALL SCREAMING]

293
00:14:46,822 --> 00:14:48,825
[GROANING]

294
00:14:54,100 --> 00:14:56,069
[GROANING]

295
00:14:56,103 --> 00:14:58,372
The ship's
going to disintegrate.

296
00:15:04,481 --> 00:15:06,484
[GROANING]

297
00:15:06,518 --> 00:15:07,820
[GRUNTING]

298
00:15:09,823 --> 00:15:12,360
[GASPS]

299
00:15:12,393 --> 00:15:14,896
We got to keep it
from going into the wormhole!

300
00:15:26,447 --> 00:15:27,915
[GRUNTING TIREDLY]

301
00:15:31,420 --> 00:15:33,924
[ASTRO AND BLUE KNIGHT GRUNTING]

302
00:15:46,576 --> 00:15:47,844
It should be okay now.

303
00:15:47,878 --> 00:15:50,114
But we have to get it
to the airport right away.

304
00:15:50,147 --> 00:15:50,949
Huh?

305
00:15:53,953 --> 00:15:56,056
The controls
are barely working now.

306
00:15:56,090 --> 00:15:57,492
What's the matter
with them?

307
00:15:57,525 --> 00:15:59,060
There was too much damage
from the wormhole.

308
00:15:59,094 --> 00:16:00,429
We're losing power.

309
00:16:00,462 --> 00:16:01,798
[WOMAN YELLS]

310
00:16:04,002 --> 00:16:05,870
All engines are down!

311
00:16:08,208 --> 00:16:10,010
O'SHAY [OVER RADIO]:
<i>Astro! We've lost power.</i>

312
00:16:10,043 --> 00:16:11,913
<i>You've got</i>
<i>to keep us in the air.</i>

313
00:16:24,064 --> 00:16:26,467
[GRUNTING]

314
00:16:26,500 --> 00:16:27,636
I'm running out of energy!

315
00:16:27,669 --> 00:16:29,672
There may not be time.

316
00:16:29,705 --> 00:16:32,243
If we can't make it
to the airport,

317
00:16:32,276 --> 00:16:34,746
we'll just have to find
somewhere else to land.

318
00:16:39,019 --> 00:16:40,821
ASTRO:
There! That's Highway Five.

319
00:16:40,855 --> 00:16:42,758
It has a 3-mile straightaway.

320
00:16:42,791 --> 00:16:45,195
It just might work!

321
00:16:45,228 --> 00:16:46,764
ASTRO [OVER RADIO]:
<i>Drop your landing gear,</i>
<i>captain.</i>

322
00:16:46,797 --> 00:16:48,767
It's going to be a bumpy ride.
You got it.

323
00:16:54,775 --> 00:16:57,613
Argh! I can't hold on!

324
00:16:57,646 --> 00:17:00,083
We're going to hit
those energy lines.

325
00:17:04,656 --> 00:17:06,292
[ELECTRICAL WHINING]

326
00:17:06,325 --> 00:17:07,560
[ELECTRICAL FIZZING]

327
00:17:07,594 --> 00:17:09,162
[YELLING]

328
00:17:19,244 --> 00:17:21,314
Oh, no!

329
00:17:21,347 --> 00:17:23,918
We can't even
see the runway!

330
00:17:25,019 --> 00:17:26,988
Astro, are you okay out there?

331
00:17:27,022 --> 00:17:29,091
So far!

332
00:17:30,961 --> 00:17:33,231
O'SHAY [OVER RADIO]:
Can you use your searchlights?

333
00:17:33,264 --> 00:17:35,935
ASTRO:
No. They're giving out on me.

334
00:17:38,038 --> 00:17:39,240
BLUE KNIGHT:
Here.

335
00:17:39,273 --> 00:17:41,276
I'll light it up.

336
00:17:41,309 --> 00:17:42,611
[GRUNTS]

337
00:17:53,294 --> 00:17:55,730
Uh, looks like
we're going to be okay now.

338
00:17:55,764 --> 00:17:57,633
Drop the emergency gear.

339
00:17:57,667 --> 00:17:59,202
FIRST OFFICER:
Roger.

340
00:17:59,235 --> 00:18:01,272
CAPTAIN:
And tell the passengers
to brace themselves.

341
00:18:18,397 --> 00:18:19,865
[ALL SCREAMING]

342
00:18:29,679 --> 00:18:32,317
There's no way out.
We've got to turn this thing.

343
00:18:36,957 --> 00:18:38,727
Captain, sharp left!

344
00:18:38,760 --> 00:18:40,695
I'll try.

345
00:18:51,178 --> 00:18:53,815
[PASSENGERS WAILING]

346
00:18:56,452 --> 00:18:59,857
Huh? We've stopped.

347
00:18:59,890 --> 00:19:00,925
[TWITTERING]

348
00:19:00,959 --> 00:19:02,194
Argh!

349
00:19:03,829 --> 00:19:05,365
I can't
believe it.

350
00:19:05,398 --> 00:19:08,135
PASSENGER:
Oh! They did it! It's over!

351
00:19:08,169 --> 00:19:12,008
[ALL CHEERING]

352
00:19:12,041 --> 00:19:13,077
PASSENGER:
The robots saved us.

353
00:19:13,110 --> 00:19:14,344
PASSENGER 2:
Whoo!

354
00:19:14,378 --> 00:19:18,417
DRAKE:
We can't do anything right!

355
00:19:18,450 --> 00:19:22,190
We may not be stronger than
the robots, but we are smarter.

356
00:19:22,223 --> 00:19:24,093
And we are not giving up.

357
00:19:24,126 --> 00:19:26,262
ASTRO:
Blue Knight,
without your help,

358
00:19:26,296 --> 00:19:30,402
none of these people
would be here right now.

359
00:19:30,435 --> 00:19:32,871
[ALL CHEERING]

360
00:19:32,905 --> 00:19:34,408
BLUE KNIGHT:
I didn't do it for them.

361
00:19:34,441 --> 00:19:36,143
You didn't?

362
00:19:36,176 --> 00:19:38,046
I did it for the robots.

363
00:19:38,079 --> 00:19:41,418
Especially the ones
the humans mistreat.

364
00:19:41,451 --> 00:19:43,020
Astro,
do you really think

365
00:19:43,053 --> 00:19:45,990
humans and robots can someday
stop all their fighting

366
00:19:46,024 --> 00:19:47,226
and work together?

367
00:19:47,259 --> 00:19:49,129
I really do.

368
00:19:49,162 --> 00:19:52,199
Even after humans caused
all this trouble for you and me?

369
00:19:52,233 --> 00:19:53,836
Uh...

370
00:19:56,072 --> 00:19:58,175
Yeah, I really do
believe in them.

371
00:19:59,410 --> 00:20:01,012
Who built you, anyway?

372
00:20:04,317 --> 00:20:07,221
Someone who's very committed
to the future of robotics.

373
00:20:08,590 --> 00:20:11,361
[DELICATE CHIMING]

374
00:20:11,394 --> 00:20:14,366
Hey! Here comes the rescue team.
Come on.

375
00:20:14,399 --> 00:20:16,802
Huh?
Where did he--?

376
00:20:16,835 --> 00:20:18,071
Oh!

377
00:20:18,104 --> 00:20:20,841
O'SHAY:
Hey! Astro!

378
00:20:20,875 --> 00:20:22,077
We're
down here!

379
00:20:22,110 --> 00:20:23,512
Doctor!

380
00:20:23,545 --> 00:20:27,057
Ah! I'm so glad you're
all right. I was worried!

381
00:20:27,090 --> 00:20:28,190
Huh?

382
00:20:28,223 --> 00:20:29,857
Where did
the Blue Knight go?

383
00:20:29,890 --> 00:20:32,357
I have no idea,
but I bet he'll be back.

384
00:20:32,390 --> 00:20:35,357
O'SHAY:
He is quite a mystery, isn't he?

385
00:20:35,390 --> 00:20:37,957
ASTRO:
Not to me.

386
00:20:41,990 --> 00:20:43,923
[♪]

